Incident.Summary: RAPID Pawn and Precious Metal Dealer Electronic Audit - TNT Chester

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText:
23-MSP-002658 RAPID Electronic Audit Pawn and Precious Metal Dealer TNT Jewelers, Chester, Queen Annes County, Maryland
ASSOCIATED CASES: 22-MSP-038833 & 19-MSP-035993

ATTACHMENT: MSP 243A, Maryland State Police, Pawn and Precious Metal, Business Regulation Article, Title 12, Electronic Audit Form
                          MSP 243B, Maryland State Police, Pawn and Precious Metal, Business Regulation Article, Title 12, Inspection Form
                         Six (6) digital photographs of paper transactions and expired licenses
                         Two (2) RAPID transaction records

    On Thursday, February 9, 2023, I, Corporal Jean L. Davenport #4718, MSP PCSD/RAPID Compliance Officer, conducted a RAPID compliance electronic audit of TNT Jewelers located in Chester, Queen Annes County, Maryand.  The audit was done electronically, and the transaction was selected based on dealer reporting data.  During a review of the transactions, the records were found not in compliance for the following reasons:

     No prices listed on transactions as per Department of Labor, Licensing, and Regulation (DLLR), Secondhand Precious Metal Object Dealers and Pawnbrokers Program handbook, prices are required:

The required information about a secondhand precious metal object includes:
A complete, accurate description of the item
Initials, monograms, or inscriptions
Metallic composition of the object
Alterations
Weight
The price paid to the seller by the dealer.
Separate entries shall be made for each item acquired

    I conducted a check of the DLLR website for license status for business' in the Chester zip code 21619 and no license was listed.  Through further investigation, a review of a previous audit of TNT Jewelers on October 8, 2022 (22-MSP-038833) revealed the TNT Jewelers DLLR license for the Chester store was suspended at that time due to a tax liability. 

   On February 9, 2023, I emailed Tanya Minion from DLLR for TNT Jewelers current license status and was advised the Chester store was not licensed, and their license expired March 9, 2022.  

   On Thursday, February 16, 2023, at approximately 1030 hours, Tanya Minion and I responded to TNT Jewelers in Chester, Queen Anne's County, MD, to conduct an audit and educational visit.    Upon arrival, we met with employee Keri Quinto (employee "KQ" on transactions entered), who advised she is primary contact at the TNT Chester store.  KQ stated she conducts the transactions at the Chester store and calls Prete who provides the price paid for the purchase.  On February 20, 2023, Tanya Minion confirmed that KQ was approved to conduct precious metal transactions for both Easton and Chester stores.  

   I then conducted an audit using the MSP 243B Inspection Form (attached), resulting in discovery of several violations of Maryland Business Title 12 and AG Statute 11 as follows:

Operating without a license (21 counts with 21 separate transaction conducted since license expired March 9, 2022)
Failure to display license (no new or expired license was on display to the public)
Failure to record amount or other considerations (14 of the 21 transactions since March 9, 2022, do not have an amount entered)
Failure to properly tag items (Transaction Number was not attached to the individual items)
Failure to store objects and records in accordance to law (transaction records were maintained in an unlocked file cabinet located in with other records)
Weights and Measures without registration (MD Department of Agriculture Weights and Measures, scale certification for Account Number 709273, expired May 31, 2016)

   KQ contacted Prete via telephone, and I advised Prete his license had expired and the Chester store could not conduct any precious metal purchases until the license was renewed and the issues corrected.  

    KQ took immediate corrective measures to record the amount on the transaction records and tag the items.  She moved the Transaction Records from the unsecured file cabinet to a lone area within the large safe.  

   I provide KQ with the Department of Agricultural website address for information on calibration and certifying the scale.  

    Based on the above facts, and past enforcement actions associated with TNT Jewelers, case open pending charge for Operating without a License.

On February 21, 2023, at approximately 1100 hours, I, Cpl. Jean L. Davenport #4718, MSP/PCSD RAPID, delivered an Application of Charges to the Queen Anne's County Commissioner for one (1) count of doing business without a license.  

On February 21, 2023, I received an email from DLLR regarding a new license issued on 2/21/2023 for TNT Chester:



On March 1, 2023, at approximately 1330 hours, I drove to TNT Easton and met Thomas Prete and issued Criminal Summons Case Number D-034-CR-23-00007.  Prete signed all three (3) copies agreeing to appear in court on March 29, 2023.  He was also provided with Notice of Advice of Rights and the Public Defenders information notice.  I then faxed the return of service to MSP Centreville.  

   Case closed.
